    "id": "half-elves",
    "nom": "Half Elves",
    "sousNom": null,
    "race": "Elven",
    "description": "Half-Elves occupy a delicate place between two worlds. Neither entirely human nor fully elven, they often embody the best—and sometimes the worst—of both lineages. Their mixed heritage grants them remarkable adaptability, whether socially, magically, or physically, but also exposes them to mistrust from purist elven communities and suspicion from humans who see them as unpredictable.\n\nHalf-Elves do not form their own nations. Instead, they grow up within human or elven societies, inheriting the cultural environment of their parents. Because of this, no two Half-Elves are alike: some display the finesse and longevity of their elven lineage, while others lean toward human resilience and ambition. Many develop the ability to navigate between cultures with surprising ease, becoming diplomats, adventurers, scouts, or intermediaries in conflicts between humans and elves.\n\nTheir dual identity sometimes creates inner conflict, leading them either to wander in search of a place they truly belong, or to embrace their hybrid nature with pride. Half-Elves are often curious, adaptable, and perceptive, capable of learning quickly and excelling in roles requiring flexibility, negotiation, or creativity.",
