    "description": "Halflings are small folk gifted with a disarming youthful appearance that makes suspicion slip right past them. Their round faces, bright eyes, and lively manners suggest innocence—even when they are far from it. This lack of perceived threat is both a blessing and a curse: they avoid trouble easily, yet they are rarely taken seriously, even when they should be.\n\nLiving mostly among human societies—and, more rarely, elven ones—Halflings blend effortlessly into larger cultures, adapting to their customs while keeping their own traditions mostly unspoken. A long-standing rumor claims they have a homeland of their own, a hidden place of green hills and cozy burrows. Halflings themselves speak of it fondly, yet none can say if it truly exists. They were taught never to seek it, as if the myth itself mattered more than the truth; a story they cling to for comfort, identity, or perhaps something deeper.\n\nBehind their cheerful faces lie sharp instincts for survival, negotiation, and quiet mischief—traits born from a life lived on the edge of obscurity.",
