    "id": "fairies",
    "nom": "Fairies",
    "sousNom": null,
    "race": "Demie",
    "description": "Fairies are graceful, winged beings roughly half the height of a human—slightly taller than Halflings yet far lighter. They are whimsical, capricious, and irresistibly curious, embracing life as a kaleidoscope of sensations and emotions. Their moods shift with the wind: playful laughter one moment, spiteful mischief the next.\n\nThough often charming, Fairies are known for their volatile tempers and their notorious inability to accept defeat. A fairy scorned may unleash a cascade of pranks, illusions, or unsettling tricks—not deadly, but certainly memorable, and sometimes genuinely dangerous. The wrath of a Fairy, once provoked, can linger far longer than expected.\n\nTheir societies favor artistic expression, freedom, and the surreal logic of dreams. Fairies wander through forests and coastal regions, dancing between sunlight and moonbeams, shaping the world subtly with their magic. They are neither benevolent nor malevolent—merely true to their nature: emotional, impulsive, and endlessly enchanted by secrets and stories.\n\nNot to be confused with pixies, which is a monstrous version of this people.",
