    "description": "Naggan are serpentfolk descended from ancient lineages that once thrived behind the protective walls of Rosaï. They are recognized by their serpentine tails, shimmering scales, and calm, deliberate manner of speech. Though humanoid in stature, their physical and spiritual heritage ties them deeply to the forgotten age when Primordial Dragons still brushed against the world.\n\nTheir society was once divided into several clans—each distinguished by scale coloration and cultural tradition. Many of these clans were decimated when Morvivance reached Rosaï, scattering survivors across Thalifen. Today, Naggan communities are small, secretive, and often hidden within remote societies where mistrust follows them like a shadow.\n\nNaggan culture venerates the Primordial Dragons not as gods, but as archetypes of cosmic principles. Each clan interprets this devotion differently: some through shamanism, others through martial discipline, mysticism, or oratory tradition. Although most Naggan now live isolated lives, the old customs endure in fragments—songs, scales dyed in ritual pigments, meditative dances, and cryptic proverbs referencing the \"Silenced Wyrms.\"\n\nDespite their enigmatic aura, Naggan are not hostile; they are contemplative and pragmatic, their worldview shaped by the belief that destiny coils and uncoils like a serpent, unpredictable yet purposeful.\n\nSome of most known naggan's clan are:",
