    "sousNom": null,
    "race": "Semie",
    "description": "Centaurans are an ancient semi-equine people whose culture blends warrior tradition with ritual wisdom. Proud and fiercely independent, they live in secluded forest enclaves where every aspect of life—craft, combat, diplomacy, even travel—is governed by elaborate customs passed down through long oral lineages. To outsiders, these customs often seem cryptic or overly formal, but to Centaurans they are the foundation of balance and honor.\n\nTheir society values strength of body as much as clarity of purpose. Centaurans rarely involve themselves in the affairs of other peoples, believing that most humanoids lack the discipline and respect necessary to navigate Centauran etiquette. Yet, when they choose to act, they do so with solemn conviction and strategic foresight.\n\nRegarded as both protectors and omens by nearby communities, Centaurans maintain an aura of mystique. They act neither as sages nor savages—simply as guardians of their own path, bound to traditions older than most written histories.\n\nNot to be confused with centaurs, which is a monstrous version of this people.",
