    "id": "ogren",
    "nom": "Ogren",
    "sousNom": null,
    "race": "Vermine",
    "description": "Ogrens are massive (gargantuan even) humanoids, descended from ancient ogres yet far more structured and civilized than their monstrous kin. Their imposing physiques, ritual markings, and sheer presence command attention. Though often perceived as brutes, Ogrens possess a practical, earthy intelligence shaped by survival rather than theory.\n\nThey inhabit harsh deserts and mountains, living in tight-knit clans centered around endurance, strength, and ancestral trials. To an Ogren, identity is earned through hardship: surviving the world is a rite in itself. While their past conflicts with other peoples have given them an intimidating reputation, those who look beyond their size discover a loyal, honest folk—remarkably skilled in stonecraft, forging, and pragmatic engineering.\n\nOgrens are towering survivors defined by durability and brute strength. Their weaknesses lie not in courage but in inner instability and a lifetime of hardship, reflected in low Balance and Luck.\n\nNot to be confused with ogre, which is a monstrous version of this people.",
