    "id": "orkkan",
    "nom": "Orkkan",
    "sousNom": null,
    "race": "Vermine",
    "description": "Orkkans, sometimes called “half-orcs,” are a warrior people shaped by relentless environments and an even harsher history. Their powerful frames, pronounced tusks, and resilient skin speak of a life defined by struggle. In Orkkan society, adversity is not merely endured—it is honored. Strength, rivalry, and tenacity form the core of their culture.\n\nPrimarily nomadic, Orkkans travel across deserts, jungles, coasts, and underground territories, adapting with surprising ease. Their long-standing conflicts with humans have created mutual mistrust, passed down through generations. Yet Orkkans are far from mindless brutes: they possess a fierce sense of honor, deep clan loyalty, and a cultural respect for those who prove themselves through action rather than words.\n\nOrkkans are fierce, fast, and durable, thriving in adversity. Their impulsiveness and tumultuous past diminish their Wisdom, Intelligence, and Luck, grounding them as proud survivors shaped by struggle.\n\nNot to be confused with orcs, which is a monstrous version of this people.",
