    "sousNom": null,
    "race": "Vermine",
    "description": "Gablins, civilized cousins of monstrous goblins, are small, sharp-minded, and irrepressibly resourceful. Quick of hand and quicker of wit, they thrive in cramped alleys, bustling cities, and subterranean networks. Their society revolves around improvisation, cunning, and adaptability—traits that let them survive where others falter.\n\nAlthough often mistrusted, Gablins maintain complex social structures based on extended families or craft-and-thief guilds. They excel in improvised engineering, erratic chemistry, stealth, negotiation, and the creative reinterpretation of ownership. Where something needs fixing, repurposing, acquiring, or quietly relocating, a Gablin is rarely far behind—usually grinning while doing it.\n\nGablins thrive on improvisation, speed, and cleverness. Their weaknesses stem from physical frailty and an inherently unstable inner nature, making them brilliant but fragile opportunists.\n\nNot to be confused with goblins, which is a monstrous version of this people.",
